module.description: Register fields should be considered static unless otherwise noted as dynamic.

bitfield.description: Reserved (read zero)
I/O strength control bit Common to all digital output pads Should be set when unregulated voltage is below approximately 2.6 V.

register.description: Select output signal on observation output 0

bitfield.description: Reserved (read zero)
Observation output 0 enable control for PC0 0: Observation output disabled 1: Observation output enabled Note: If enabled, this overwrites the standard GPIO behavior of PC0.
n - obs_sigs[n] output on output 0: 0: rfc_obs_sig0 1: rfc_obs_sig1 2: rfc_obs_sig2 Others: Reserved

Set to 1 to connect the temperature sensor to the SOC_ADC. See also RFCORE_XREG_ATEST register description to enable the temperature sensor.
Software should not rely on the value of a reserved bit. To provide compatibility with future products, the value of a reserved bit should be preserved across a read-modify-write operation.
Reserved (read zero)

USB PHY stand-by override bit When this bit is cleared to 0 (default state) the USB module cannot change the stand-by mode of the PHY (USB pads) and the PHY is forced out of stand-by mode. This bit must be 1 as well as the stand-by control from the USB controller, before the mode of the PHY is stand-by.
